            <div type="commentary">
                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->
                    <!--50cm H, by 30 cm wide, by 18 cm deep. A brief edition of a funerary stele, recovered in an emergency excavation by Giovanni di Stefano (date not specified), from the area of the necropolis in località Bellaccio, excavated in 1896 and 1909/1910 by Orsi and Pace (1.5-2km outside the inhabited centre). This stele cannot be directly associated with a tomb / burial. A sandstone stele 50cm high, with Neon son of Donax ΝΕΩΝ ΔΟΝΑΚΟΣ, apparently then repeated below in less skilled letters, and some errors, and with some further letters lower down the stone. Letters of C4 BC. Names are common / well attested. Suggestion is that the letters below the first two lines are a sort of exercise by a less skilled lapicide, but this is not entirely satisfactory as an explanation and the photographs are not adequate to enable a proper control of the text presented – the difficulty of reading the lines below makes the interpretation open to some doubt, even if it seems reasonable to suggest that everything from line 3 onwards was carved by a different hand.--></p>
            </div>
